      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUEEN ERA (8) was quickly out of the boxes with a slick early sectional clocking 22.90 with a 1.75 lengths win at Richmond over 401m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Ideally placed to take this out. IRINKA ALANA (1) is a well performed dog and winner of 11 races who is worth forgiving after finishing out of the placings at Temora (25.91). Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Should play a prominent role. TENACIOUS TALKER (6) is better than last start when fourth (30.22) from Box 3 at this track over 520m. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Should be about the money. ZIPPING MARQUEZ (2) was in the money last start and likely to feature again.",
